 GADGETS

  > List View

  That  one  is not supported yet - I've problems with allocating new nodes
when proggy is running. But, will be fixed soon.

  > Dice module

  Looks fine, right ?  So pick desired combination of dices and roll'em !
If there's sth in 'Custom' gadget, it'll be used instead of MX settings.
Custom dice format is ?d?? , where ? is number of dices to roll, and ?? is
type of dice (from 1 to ???).
  If you'll enter ?d , then you'll get ?d<value from right MX>, and if
  d? , you'll get <value from left MX>d?. Wise, isn't it ? (Thx Eric :)
  Btw, enterig ??? will cause DMA to roll 1d???.
Don't be silly, and don't try to enter junk such as '3v2q45b253BW' *grin*
Clr gadget clears Custom gadget, so tou don't have to do it from keyboard.

  > Clock module

  Works  properly.  Maybe 'About' mode is not fully random, but I'm working
on that. 'About' dithering is currently set to 10%, but as  soon  as  Prefs
will be completed, you'll can set it to whatever you want.

  > Sound Machine
'Sound' plays standard IFF sample. Feel free  to  send  me  your  own  cool
samples :] 'Sound' uses DSound © 1991-1992 by Dave Schreiber. When Prefs'll
be done, you'll can use any of sound players you got.
'Play'  plays  standard ???Tracker module.  Dunno exactly what versions are
supported.   There's a @{"bug" link bugs} - when you choose file other than
module  Amiga  will  die.   I'll  try  to  fix  it  as soon as it's humanly
possible. Also working on depacking powerpacked modules.
(I'm not sure if it would be better to use external  module  player  -  the
one I got isn't really good *sigh* - send me useful player, maybe ? :)
@endnode

